laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver is of normal size and normal signal intensity. Gallbladder is full of stones with a thickened wall. No evidence of significant pericholecystic hepatic enhancement. No intrahepatic bile duct dilatation. CBD not dilated. An anatomical variant with an aberrant right posterior duct draining into the common hepatic duct. Pancreas of normal size and intensity. Mucosal enhancement and small amount of periduodenal edema around the second and third portion of the duodenum. Adrenals, spleen, kidneys appear unremarkable. No evidence of retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. No free fluid in abdomen.
